<item>
            <title>[LU-17129] sanity-sec: cleanup fileset info on nodemaps</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17129</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In sanity-sec, when fileset info is added to nodemaps via the &lt;tt&gt;set_param -P&lt;/tt&gt; command, it needs to be removed afterwards with &lt;tt&gt;set_param -P -d&lt;/tt&gt;. Otherwise, these commands remain on the llogs, even after nodemaps have been deleted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
